## 6. Security (Article 32)

The Processor implements appropriate technical and organisational measures, including:

- Encryption of Personal Data in transit and at rest.
- Ability to ensure ongoing confidentiality, integrity, availability, and resilience of processing systems.
- Process for regularly testing, assessing and evaluating the effectiveness of those measures.
- Pseudonymisation and access controls per role.

## 7. Personal data breach (Articles 33-34)

The Processor notifies the Controller of any Personal Data breach without
undue delay and in any event within 48 hours of becoming aware, with all
information reasonably needed for the Controller to meet its Art. 33
notification obligation to the supervisory authority (72 hours).

## 8. Data Protection Impact Assessment (Article 35)

The Processor provides reasonable assistance to the Controller for any DPIA
required and for prior consultation with the supervisory authority (Art. 36).

## 9. Records (Article 30(2))

The Processor maintains a record of all categories of processing activities
carried out on behalf of the Controller and makes it available on request.

## 10. Term and termination

This DPA remains in force for as long as the Processor processes Personal Data on behalf of the Controller.

